SIMPLE: hyalonema
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyalonema
<hw>Hy`a*lo*ne"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"y`alos</grk> glass + <?/ a thread.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of hexactinelline sponges, having a long stem composed of
very long, slender, transparent, siliceous fibres twisted together like
the strands of a color. The stem of the Japanese species (<spn>Hyalonema
Sieboldii</spn>), called <stype>glass-rope</stype>, has long been in use
as an ornament. See <er>Glass-rope</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyalophane</ent>⟦br⟧
